            <Title>Gameplay</Title>
            <Text>Setup

Each player defined two events, and writes them down on index cards, these events will occur during play
The invasion of the spire will have one wave per player
Put events into a logical order, two per wave, both of a player’s events cannot be in the same wave
Select an event in the wave, that player get the spotlight, they frame the scene in which the event occurs. Other players create threats surrounding the event, threats are rated based on the wave they are in. The last wave contains threats of rating 5, stepping down one for each preceding wave.
Each player is responsible for threats they created
A player’s champion cannot confront a threat they created

Taking Action

Describe what you intend to accomplish
Dice pool
For each trait group select a trait if relevant, with it add a layer of detail to your action
Roll the dice
Each number greater than three is a hit
Dead a number of hits equal to the threat to eliminate it
If total hits are less than threat level, take stress equal to the difference
Expending magical power can be used to add additional dice, one for one with accompanying description
Expending Magical Power
Rather than rolling dice, magical power can be expended to defeat threats, for each point of magical energy add a layer of detail on the action

The Wager

Whenever dice are rolled a player may wager magical power, in essence trying to use their power to salvage unclaimed power lingering in the world. The player selected which numbers to wager on, and an amount of power to bet. If any of the dice show the number wager on the player claims power equal to the number of dice showing the number ties their wager.

Resolving Questions

Players should frame scenes so that they have an opportunity to resolve the questions on their character sheets. By resolving a question, the player receive a fate chip. Fate chips can be used to lower the result required for a hit on a role.

Action Order

Select the champion or threat that most logically goes first
After that player goes they may choose a threat of champion to go next, etc…
All champions and threats must act before a new round begins

